<font color="#FF0000">A MEMORIAL DAY &quot;THANKS&quot;</font><br>
<tt>Mon May 26  0:11:35 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
This is my first Memorial Day since I have &quot;come home&quot;.<br><br>
I no longer bury my Vietnam Veteran past in a grave of shame, fear, and humiliation.<br><br>
I am a Vietnam Veteran, and I will proudly wear that distinction henceforth.<br><br>
To all those who have given of themselves on these pages, you have all helped me in some way to realize who and what I am with respect and dignity despite our differences, large and small.<br><br>
To everyone, I give my sincere thanks, and hope that we all can find peace.
